      "feedback": "The proposed plan addresses the corrupted GPG key issue by removing the corrupted file, downloading the correct key from the official Red Hat website, importing it, and verifying installation. This approach will resolve the vulnerability and follows the standard remediation procedure.",
      "concerns": [
        "The plan does not specify which exact URL to download the key from, which could lead to downloading from an untrusted source if the user chooses incorrectly",
